	<h1><strong>This is a report/guide on how to organize BBQ for CS GSA</strong></h1>
<h2><strong>  created by Tom Torsney-Weir for the future generations of grad students</strong></h2>
<h2> </h2>
<h2><br /><strong>## Preplanning</strong></h2>
<p>* The department has a grill which works pretty well just <br /> make sure there's gas.<br />* There are 2 gas canisters one which is brand new and unused as of<br /> July 2012.<br />* Before the event I sent out a questionaire asking who was planning on<br /> attending, what food restrictions they had, and for volunteers to help<br /> with cooking, setup, and takedown.<br />* we scheduled the event from 12-2:30.<br />* Held in north atrium (outdoors area by ASB renaissance)<br />* sent out an initial email a week before with a link to the form and then<br /> a reminder the day before<br />* total budget was $300<br />* The CSGSA has a lot of things like cups, plates, etc so ask for those so you<br /> don't have to purchase them</p>
<h2><strong>### Volunteers</strong></h2>
<p>* 1 person for help shopping<br />* 3 cooks: enough so that each person cooked for one hour<br /> (cooking starting 30 minutes early).<br />* 2-3 volunteers for setup/takedown.<br /> * Bring food out<br /> * Put food on tables</p>
<h2><strong>### Booking space/tables</strong></h2>
<p>* Space is booked through FAS office<br />* Tables are booked through facilities which ??? in the CS office <br /> can help you fill out a form</p>
<h2><strong>### Accessories needed</strong></h2>
<p>* Spatula<br />* Tongs<br />* Grill scraper<br />* Large knife<br />* Serving plates<br />* cups<br />* plates<br />* napkins<br />* knives/forks/spoons<br />* car to get propane</p>
<h1><strong>## Food</strong></h1>
